@page "/theme-kit"
@rendermode InteractiveServer

<PageTitle>ThemeKit - The Nerd Collective</PageTitle>

<div class="mb-6">
    <MudText Typo="Typo.h3" GutterBottom="true">ThemeKit</MudText>
    <MudText Typo="Typo.subtitle1">MudBlazor theme switcher, light/dark mode, and design-token editor</MudText>
</div>

<MudAlert Severity="Severity.Info" Class="mb-6">
    <MudText Typo="Typo.body2">
        ThemeKit ships as two packages: <code>TheNerdCollective.Blazor.ThemeKit</code> (services and contracts)
        and <code>TheNerdCollective.MudComponents.ThemeKit</code> (UI components).
        Live integration is demonstrated in the Billetsalg Playbook (Storybook).
    </MudText>
</MudAlert>

<MudText Typo="Typo.h5" GutterBottom="true">Components</MudText>
<MudSimpleTable Dense Striped Class="mb-6">
    <thead>
        <tr>
            <th>Component</th>
            <th>Purpose</th>
        </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
        <tr>
            <td><code>MudThemeProviderSync</code></td>
            <td>Binds <code>MudThemeProvider</code> to <code>IMudThemeStateService</code></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><code>MudThemeToolbar</code></td>
            <td>Theme switcher, mode toggle, and editor drawer (respects <code>IThemeEditorGate</code>)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><code>MudThemeTokenEditor</code></td>
            <td>Edit v1 palette, border radius, and font tokens; copy C# export</td>
        </tr>
    </tbody>
</MudSimpleTable>

<MudText Typo="Typo.h5" GutterBottom="true">Step 1: Register services</MudText>
<MudPaper Class="pa-4 mb-4">
    <pre style="background:#f5f5f5;padding:12px;border-radius:4px;border-left:4px solid #2196F3;"><code>services.AddSingleton&lt;IMudThemeCatalog, MyThemeCatalog&gt;();
services.AddMudThemeKit(options =&gt;
{
    options.DefaultThemeId = "my-default";
    options.PlaybookMode = false; // true in Storybook / Playbook
});</code></pre>
</MudPaper>

<MudText Typo="Typo.h5" GutterBottom="true">Step 2: Wire layout</MudText>
<MudPaper Class="pa-4 mb-4">
    <pre style="background:#f5f5f5;padding:12px;border-radius:4px;border-left:4px solid #4CAF50;"><code>&lt;MudThemeProviderSync /&gt;
&lt;MudThemeKitInitializer /&gt;
&lt;!-- in app bar or toolbar area --&gt;
&lt;MudThemeToolbar /&gt;</code></pre>
</MudPaper>

<MudText Typo="Typo.h5" GutterBottom="true">Environment gating</MudText>
<MudPaper Class="pa-4 mb-4">
    <MudText Typo="Typo.body2" Class="mb-3">
        The token editor is enabled in <code>Development</code>, <code>Test</code>, and <code>Staging</code>,
        or when <code>Ui:ThemeEditor:Enabled</code> is <code>true</code> in configuration.
        Production hides the editor unless explicitly overridden.
    </MudText>
</MudPaper>

<MudText Typo="Typo.h5" GutterBottom="true">Requirements</MudText>
<MudPaper Class="pa-4">
    <ul>
        <li>MudBlazor 9.5+</li>
        <li>Host-provided <code>IMudThemeCatalog</code> with one or more <code>MudThemeDescriptor</code> entries</li>
        <li>Theme definitions as plain <code>MudTheme</code> C# (no MudX / Bootswatch dependency)</li>
    </ul>
</MudPaper>
